---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base>
  <section class="section hero">
    <h1 class="hero-name">Alfie McGlennon</h1>
    <p class="hero-sub">MSc Climate Change &amp; AI // University of Reading</p>
  </section>

  <section class="section about">
    <p>
      My MSc dissertation builds a copula-based framework for predicting
      compound heat stress risk across European regions. The approach uses a
      multiplicative decomposition that separates compound hazard bias in
      climate models into a marginal component and a dependence component,
      then trains XGBoost to predict Kendall&rsquo;s tau dependence from
      large-scale atmospheric circulation patterns. The data comes from ERA5
      reanalysis, CMIP6 projections, and the Destination Earth climate digital
      twin.
    </p>
    <p>
      I&rsquo;m targeting roles in climate risk analytics and reinsurance,
      particularly at Swiss Re and Munich Re, or in operational meteorology
      adjacent to ECMWF. The through-line across my work is applying machine
      learning and statistical methods to climate data where the outputs have
      operational or commercial value.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2 class="section-heading">Projects</h2>

    <article class="project">
      <h3 class="project-title">Compound heat stress risk modelling</h3>
      <p class="project-desc">
        Copula-based bivariate framework for temperature and humidity extremes
        across European regions. Multiplicative decomposition of compound
        hazard bias with ML-driven dependence correction.
      </p>
      <p class="project-tech">Python, xarray, scipy, XGBoost, ERA5, CMIP6, DestinE</p>
    </article>

    <article class="project">
      <h3 class="project-title">
        <a href="https://alfiemcglennon.github.io/gb-grid-tool/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GB Grid Scenario Tool</a>
      </h3>
      <p class="project-desc">
        Interactive transmission grid model built from public NESO data. 27
        TNUoS zones, DC power flow with real backbone reactances, three
        dispatch modes. Validated against NESO transfer capabilities (B6F
        within 2%).
      </p>
      <p class="project-tech">JavaScript, Leaflet, WebAssembly, ERA5</p>
    </article>

    <article class="project">
      <h3 class="project-title">RL grid dispatch agents</h3>
      <p class="project-desc">
        PPO agents trained on 9 years of GB generation data to learn dispatch
        strategies from scratch. MLP, CNN, and 27-zone zonal architectures.
        Went from spending 30B/year to within 6% of real grid operations.
      </p>
      <p class="project-tech">Python, Stable Baselines3, SLURM, ERA5</p>
    </article>

    <article class="project">
      <h3 class="project-title">Quantum ML for atmospheric regression</h3>
      <p class="project-desc">
        Variational quantum circuits applied to ERA5 temperature fields and
        the Lorenz &rsquo;63 system. Fourier decomposition as an
        interpretability tool for per-qubit structured VQC regression.
      </p>
      <p class="project-tech">Python, PennyLane, ERA5</p>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2 class="section-heading">Stack</h2>
    <div class="stack">
      <p class="stack-row">
        <span class="stack-label">Languages:</span>
        <span class="stack-value">Python, JavaScript/TypeScript, Bash</span>
      </p>
      <p class="stack-row">
        <span class="stack-label">ML &amp; stats:</span>
        <span class="stack-value">XGBoost, scikit-learn, Stable Baselines3, PyTorch, PennyLane, copula methods, scipy</span>
      </p>
      <p class="stack-row">
        <span class="stack-label">Climate &amp; geo:</span>
        <span class="stack-value">xarray, ERA5, CMIP6, UKCP18, DestinE, cartopy, cdsapi</span>
      </p>
      <p class="stack-row">
        <span class="stack-label">Infrastructure:</span>
        <span class="stack-value">SLURM, Linux, Git, LaTeX</span>
      </p>
      <p class="stack-row">
        <span class="stack-label">Web:</span>
        <span class="stack-value">Astro, Leaflet, D3.js, WebAssembly</span>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section links">
    <a href="https://github.com/AlfieMcGlennon" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a>
    <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/alfred-mcglennon-927589253/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">LinkedIn</a>
  </section>
</Base>
